Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.43,0:00:18.40,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.89,0:01:46.82,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 11 - Our Small House
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.50,0:01:57.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After everything that happened, we finally\Nmade it to the hill, overlooking all of Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.58,0:02:00.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,However, the place we were looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.09,0:02:02.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,there was hardly a handful of houses or roads.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.73,0:02:05.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The rest was untouched meadows,\Ntrees and the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.90,0:02:09.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Adelaide was still rather a city-to-be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.80,0:02:18.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think we'll find our house fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.84,0:02:21.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you listen to what dad said?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.25,0:02:24.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The entrance is marked with a red bow-knot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:27.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But what I'm asking is where this house at?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.08,0:02:28.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As for where...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.01,0:02:32.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,According to this map, it should be\Nnear the river, on Polly Street. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.78,0:02:34.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Polly Street, that's a sweet name.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.99,0:02:35.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.00,0:02:38.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, is this Polly Street nearby?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.87,0:02:40.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting very tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.54,0:02:42.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we keep going this way, we won't miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.84,0:02:44.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, hold out for just a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.70,0:03:04.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It appears, we've arrived at Polly Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.50,0:03:06.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we ask someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.35,0:03:08.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you see them? That someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.71,0:03:22.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like that! Keep walking straight, you slacker!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.01,0:03:29.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bard, I can by no means see\Nhow this ox can be considered slacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:32.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as I stop encouraging him like this,\Nhe'll turn into a slacker. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:37.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're right. Personally, though,\NI don't see the point in demanding so much from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.47,0:03:39.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I do see the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.53,0:03:41.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess you value this ox greatly. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:46.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right. Mighty valuable fella to me.\NAin't you, little one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.21,0:03:51.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is it still a very long way to Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.70,0:03:53.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not all that terribly long anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.98,0:03:55.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.37,0:03:57.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.32,0:04:01.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The girls must have already arrived\Nto our new house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.20,0:04:03.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. About time they arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.98,0:04:16.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The red bow-knot is definitely there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.45,0:04:19.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think this could really be our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.12,0:04:20.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.30,0:04:23.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But dad never said he bought a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.54,0:04:25.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Only that he bought a shack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.51,0:04:29.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, are you saying that one is our house?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.50,0:04:30.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be not it? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.00,0:04:33.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, can you believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.13,0:04:35.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That run-down shack is our new home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.74,0:04:37.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:41.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then you tell me, sis.\NAre you sure this is Polly Street?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.41,0:04:42.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It probably is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:47.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.41,0:04:49.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.69,0:04:55.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.10,0:05:05.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go ask people from that house if it is. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.61,0:05:09.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You two go there, I'm so worn-out\NI can't do no more walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.69,0:05:14.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, you think that shack\Nis our new home, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.90,0:05:16.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to think so, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.86,0:05:18.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Someone from that house just showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.39,0:05:22.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks to be some woman, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.89,0:05:27.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go ask her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.70,0:05:31.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going along!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.50,0:05:46.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've finally arrived, Marsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:49.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like this would be our new house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.42,0:05:51.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rather tiny house, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.04,0:06:01.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could you be Mr. Popple's daughters, by chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.50,0:06:04.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.12,0:06:10.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for you.\NAre you Clara?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:11.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.00,0:06:15.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Ms. Mack. Jane Mac.\NI live in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.92,0:06:17.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I'm your neighbor now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.14,0:06:21.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means... That shack\Nreally is our house, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:24.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Houses are still sparse in our Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.31,0:06:26.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This shack may look tiny indeed,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.79,0:06:30.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm sure your father\Nwill make it big and glorious over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.38,0:06:32.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Had our dad said so himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.62,0:06:36.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, back when he made up his mind\Nto buy this house the other day. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.50,0:06:38.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And about us coming, too? 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.90,0:06:41.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "I might send children ahead."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.98,0:06:44.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But wasn't it three of you who came?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.68,0:06:46.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May is resting over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.19,0:06:49.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means you must be Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.01,0:06:50.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.02,0:06:52.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You girls must be pretty hungry, I reckon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.30,0:06:53.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.31,0:06:56.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're making bread now,\NI'll bring you some when it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.02,0:06:58.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You've not entered that house yet, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.69,0:07:02.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest, we never expected it\Nto be that tiny a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.47,0:07:04.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You just need to bear with it for some while. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.23,0:07:08.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you should just go check out the insides.\NI'll be joining you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.32,0:07:10.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot, madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.59,0:07:12.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.68,0:07:39.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even the floor is barely nailed. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.79,0:07:42.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father, what were you thinking,\Nbuying this house? 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.63,0:07:43.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"Shack," remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.30,0:07:54.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can see the river!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.69,0:07:55.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.49,0:08:03.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least the water situation is sorted out here. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.99,0:08:06.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If what the grandma next door said is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.23,0:08:09.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,dad's planning to turn this\Ninto a big and glorious house one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.60,0:08:12.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps building a new one from the ground up\Nwould've been easier...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.71,0:08:13.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.89,0:08:17.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should clean it up a bit\Nbefore dad and the others arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.43,0:08:19.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason, I'm not one bit\Nin the mood for cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.43,0:08:22.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yay! I'm saved, saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.80,0:08:26.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm so worn out,\NI'd much rather take an afternoon nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:27.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In this house?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.51,0:08:30.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Na-ah. Underneath that big tree over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.49,0:08:36.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea. That place looks way more\Ncomfortable for sleeping. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.08,0:08:37.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll take a little nap, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.89,0:08:39.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you two hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:42.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it,\NI'm a bit hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.71,0:08:46.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our neighbor Mrs. Mac said she'd be so kind\Nas to bring us some bread, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.49,0:08:47.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Bread?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.48,0:08:48.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.09,0:08:51.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's open!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.79,0:08:55.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Freshly baked bread!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:56.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:08:59.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.29,0:09:02.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! It smells so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.10,0:09:07.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you bake this yourself, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:09.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.\NAnd you must be Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.92,0:09:10.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.09,0:09:14.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Baking bread and other sweets is my passion. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.19,0:09:17.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Starting today, we're neighbors,\Nso let's all get along, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.45,0:09:18.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.60,0:09:20.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This place doesn't have a table either,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.58,0:09:23.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,so wouldn't it be better to lunch\Nwhile sitting on the grass outside? 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.64,0:09:24.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.30,0:09:50.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's been literal ages\Nsince we've eaten any bread that good!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.71,0:09:53.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You must be an expert bread-baker,\Nare you, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.39,0:09:55.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. If you developed such a liking for it, 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.97,0:09:59.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,why don't I treat you to some of my bread\Nevery now and then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.38,0:10:00.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please do!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.55,0:10:03.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate! Learn some shame, you. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.38,0:10:04.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.79,0:10:09.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As much as I would have liked to chat with you\Nfor a little longer, I have to go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:10.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.87,0:10:13.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My husband wasn't feeling too well,\Nso he went to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.29,0:10:20.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She does that for us\Neven while her husband is ill... 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.60,0:10:22.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She must be a very caring person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:26.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even though our shack is so ugly,\NI'm glad we have a nice neighbor, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.98,0:10:31.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lucy-May, we'll probably have to sleep\Ninside a barrel here as well, won't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.35,0:10:33.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way we can all sleep in there. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.19,0:10:35.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we've left the barrel behind! 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.39,0:10:37.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll find another one, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.15,0:10:39.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This here is not the seashore, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:41.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you suppose a barrel like that\Ncould fall from the sky? 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.90,0:10:44.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that means sleeping in a tent, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.40,0:10:48.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to sleep right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.39,0:10:54.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sleepy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:03.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have preferred a proper house\Nat least the size of Mrs. Mac's. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.69,0:11:23.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh, hmm? Now this is much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.69,0:11:26.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, then. I'll stay here for a while\Nto catch a shuteye.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.78,0:11:29.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, are you not going\Nto return to England?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.09,0:11:32.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, returning is now out of my reach. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.59,0:11:34.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But for how long? 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.50,0:11:37.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That ship wasn't the only one\Nyou could use to return to England. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:40.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They'll let you board\Nif you explain your situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.69,0:11:44.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was God's decision\Nthat I should be late to the ship. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.06,0:11:46.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I made up my mind.\NI'm staying in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.59,0:11:49.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But don't you have a wife and kids back home?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.39,0:11:52.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My missus had joined god ages ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.79,0:11:56.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And my son enlisted in the army\Nand doesn't come home anymore. 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.02,0:11:56.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.90,0:11:59.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course, I'll write a letter to son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.82,0:12:02.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll let him know I moved to Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.19,0:12:05.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I should open a practice\Nright here, in this barrel? 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.89,0:12:08.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well if you've seriously\Nmade up your mind to stay,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.89,0:12:11.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't it be better\Nto go to Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.59,0:12:12.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.78,0:12:15.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You mean, what they call the capital\Nof Southern Australia state?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.11,0:12:21.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Maybe I should go to Adelaide then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.32,0:12:25.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Before long, I'm also moving to Adelaide,\Ntogether with these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:30.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All right. In that case,\NI'm going to Adelaide with you as soon as I can. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:35.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, where do you think\NI should go to get something to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.28,0:12:53.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tob, you should calm down at least a bit,\Ndad is very tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.09,0:12:56.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing. Besides, which one of us is more tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.91,0:12:59.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine. We're already in Adelaide, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.64,0:13:01.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, on the outskirts of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.91,0:13:15.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, that there is the River Torrens.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.21,0:13:18.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our shack should be\Naround there, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.78,0:13:21.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to live near the river,\Nfor different reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.60,0:13:25.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let me reiterate it once again\Nthat you'll be disappointed at the sight of our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.58,0:13:27.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, that's one shabby kind of house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.01,0:13:30.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.81,0:13:35.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I promise that I won't be disappointed,\Neven if it's the ugliest home I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.59,0:13:36.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.90,0:13:57.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.37,0:14:00.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.59,0:14:06.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate and the girls\Nare running out of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.99,0:14:08.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, that there is our...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:10.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,See? What did I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.10,0:14:13.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I asked you\Nnot to be too disappointed...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.73,0:14:16.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,More than disappointed,\NI'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.00,0:14:19.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's one tiny house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.98,0:14:26.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We arrived here three hours before you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.64,0:14:28.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, that soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.24,0:14:29.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what have you been up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.50,0:14:30.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've taken a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.92,0:14:32.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear, were you that tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.85,0:14:35.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, have you met\Nour neighbor, Mrs. Mac?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.31,0:14:38.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A mighty kind lady.\NShe treated us to some bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.10,0:14:41.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to hear that.\NBut where's Clara?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.78,0:14:43.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Went to fetch water from the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.81,0:14:45.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you got no bucket, no nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.60,0:14:47.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Mac lent us a bucket.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.89,0:14:55.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.68,0:15:03.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.70,0:15:06.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.29,0:15:08.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I've ever seen you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.69,0:15:11.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's because this is the first time we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.32,0:15:13.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.19,0:15:16.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Bernard.\NBernard Mosley.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.79,0:15:18.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Clara Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.64,0:15:20.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.29,0:15:23.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That means Mr. Popple\Nhad also arrived to Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.38,0:15:26.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know my father?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.01,0:15:29.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. To tell you the truth, I was the one\Nwho showed him that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.68,0:15:30.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.71,0:15:33.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So you were the one who foisted\Nthat run-down cabin on him! 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.38,0:15:34.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:36.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like that! It really isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.39,0:15:38.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.99,0:15:43.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, that house and plot\Nall belonged to government!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:47.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That house belonged to Mr. Simpson, who joined\Nthe exploration party and went out into the hinterland.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.85,0:15:50.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what happened to Mr. Simpson after? 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:52.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He never returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.47,0:15:55.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, while one the expedition,\Nhe got sick and passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.00,0:15:58.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And he didn't have any relatives either?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.20,0:15:59.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least not in Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.01,0:16:02.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, that house\Nreturned to the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:05.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I proposed\Nfor Mr. Popple to buy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.86,0:16:08.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The plot he got is even more\Nimportant than the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:11.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After all, what I wanted the most\Nis for our neighbors to be good people. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.53,0:16:14.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your neighbors?\NThen, that makes you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.55,0:16:16.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Mac's little brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.10,0:16:19.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I work in Colonel Light's office.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.48,0:16:22.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I finally know the full story. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.70,0:16:25.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Aren't you cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.82,0:16:26.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.59,0:16:28.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though you're shivering a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.34,0:16:32.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've been swimming for quite some while,\Nso I was thinking of getting out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.07,0:16:33.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then you should get out quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.11,0:16:36.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.80,0:16:41.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well if you wish to keep swimming, go ahead.\NI won't ask you to get out against your will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.06,0:16:43.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that! The thing is, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.19,0:16:45.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm stark naked!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.56,0:16:46.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.39,0:16:48.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I left my clothes on that tree branch\Nright next to you. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.40,0:16:51.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.59,0:17:00.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.18,0:17:03.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you want me to carry that bucket for you,\Nwait for me just a little ahead on the road!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.60,0:17:07.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, start walking, you slacker!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.06,0:17:09.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like that! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.39,0:17:14.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That man is being unreasonably harsh with it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.10,0:17:16.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's in his habit now. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.00,0:17:18.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's a nasty habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.01,0:17:23.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just carry inside the house\Nthe stuff we immediately need. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.01,0:17:25.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The stuff that we don't need urgently,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.21,0:17:28.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, we could just sheet it and leave it outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.39,0:17:32.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We really can't bring anything at all\Ninside a house that small... 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.48,0:17:33.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You have my promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.80,0:17:36.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll expand it with at least\Ntwo more rooms as soon as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.58,0:17:39.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even two more rooms won't suffice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.30,0:17:41.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying we won't have two rooms for long. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:48.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You've arrived rather soon. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.56,0:17:50.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Is this water good for drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.78,0:17:52.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was suitable...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.89,0:17:54.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But there was a person swimming in the river. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.08,0:17:57.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Someone was swimming? Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:17:59.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I see everyone had arrived?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.80,0:18:04.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, mother, this here is our neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.23,0:18:06.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you, I'm Bernard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.48,0:18:09.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I live next door,\Ntogether with my sister and her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.12,0:18:10.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.76,0:18:13.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple! We've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.79,0:18:16.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thanks for everything. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.19,0:18:19.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if my family seems to have developed\Nan universal aversion for this house. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.88,0:18:21.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.39,0:18:24.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It hadn't been used for quite a while\Nand fell into ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.11,0:18:29.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Considering it was you who proposed it to me,\Nthat sounds mighty irresponsible of you. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:32.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's not get so worked up. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.02,0:18:35.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you say it yourself,\N"Anything would do," Mr. Popple?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.81,0:18:38.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With just a bit of work,\Nit'll become unrecognizable. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.58,0:18:40.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also going to help you\Nwith whatever I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.79,0:18:42.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Out of neighbor's reciprocity. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.49,0:18:45.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, now that you mention it,\NI remembered I've got a favor to ask right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.77,0:18:50.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If that wouldn't trouble you too much,\Ncould you lent me a bit of a hand in stretching the tent?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.31,0:18:51.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was rather quick. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.94,0:18:54.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bernard might be very busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.18,0:18:56.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, I only have\Nwomen and children here with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.94,0:18:57.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:02.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... No. For certain, I {\i1}will{\i0} help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.22,0:19:07.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait, Sticky!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.60,0:19:09.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.30,0:19:12.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sticky!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.28,0:19:16.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're telling you to stop! You!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.40,0:19:19.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How about this? 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.31,0:19:23.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on tight, Kate!\NYou {\i1}cannot{\i0} let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.68,0:19:29.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, do something.\NDo something soon, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:31.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.09,0:19:38.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you even want to run away from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.67,0:19:41.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It seems we can't keep her unleashed after all. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.63,0:19:44.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems. Well, let's go back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.79,0:19:45.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.89,0:19:56.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And don't try to run away ever again, Sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.70,0:19:57.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.83,0:19:59.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, Sticky!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.30,0:20:03.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, start walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.48,0:20:07.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.49,0:20:09.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.59,0:20:20.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Move, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.09,0:20:22.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch-ouch-ouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.82,0:20:25.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Sure is stubborn, our Sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.55,0:20:27.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:31.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like she wants to go somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.18,0:20:34.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe there are other goats this way\Nor something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.29,0:20:40.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! I know, Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.40,0:20:41.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.67,0:20:42.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where Sticky wants to go
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.43,0:20:45.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,is that clearing yonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.08,0:20:48.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.26,0:20:49.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, to the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.54,0:20:51.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She must've smelled the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.37,0:20:54.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? You were just feeling thirsty?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.87,0:20:59.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Sticky!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.65,0:21:02.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like that is good?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.92,0:21:04.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Wait a moment, Mr. Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.80,0:21:06.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. Just a little back. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.69,0:21:10.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, now press it down real hard, will you?\NI need it stretched. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:15.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.12,0:21:16.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.42,0:21:17.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.38,0:21:19.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Wait! Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.22,0:21:23.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's dark! 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.76,0:21:28.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you ain't awfully reliable guy, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.29,0:21:31.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Mr. Popple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.22,0:21:32.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.58,0:21:37.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for looking after my children today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.64,0:21:38.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mention it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.97,0:21:42.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, isn't it Bernard underneath there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.99,0:21:44.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.43,0:21:47.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how cruel of you!\NCan't you tell by looking?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.02,0:21:49.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm helping to stretch the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.30,0:21:51.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I highly doubt it somehow. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.19,0:21:53.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, I can't bring you\Nto do any house maintenance. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.79,0:21:57.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are various reasons behind this... 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.89,0:21:59.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't believe it either. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.30,0:22:01.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.92,0:22:07.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is Mrs. Jane Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.80,0:22:11.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mrs. Mac, I'm Mr. Popple's missus. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.80,0:22:15.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Children told me about what you did for us.\NThank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.01,0:22:17.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. I didn't do anything in the least special.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.89,0:22:21.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, we are neighbors from now on,\Nso I would be happy to help with anything. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.96,0:22:24.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The feeling is mutual.\NFeel free to ask us of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.98,0:22:28.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In a place like this,\Nif we don't look after each other, 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.11,0:22:30.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,any unforeseen difficulty\Nwould render us paralyzed. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.07,0:22:34.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's exactly what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.18,0:22:35.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.81,0:22:36.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.39,0:22:40.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear something just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.81,0:22:43.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a shriek of a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.50,0:22:45.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Kate and Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.30,0:22:46.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.30,0:22:53.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's dangerous, Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.22,0:22:54.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Stop resisting, Sticky! 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.82,0:22:57.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You'll fall into the river!\NCalm down, Sticky!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.02,0:23:01.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't hold you any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.19,0:23:02.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.19,0:23:03.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They fell down!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.61,0:23:06.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:10.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sticky!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.00,0:23:16.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of the goat, Lucy-May!\NLest you'll also get swept away!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.11,0:23:20.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! Let go of the goat, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.60,0:23:23.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I cant! Can't! 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.08,0:23:24.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.88,0:23:31.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here! Here, stretch you hand, Lucy-May!\NCatch on to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.51,0:23:34.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Kate! Help! Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.97,0:23:36.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.48,0:23:43.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Sister! Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.05,0:23:45.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on there, Lucy-May! 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.99,0:23:47.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.73,0:23:50.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.99,0:23:56.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Someone! Help us!\NSomeone, come here, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.33,0:23:59.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.69,0:24:08.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The one who saved me and the goat\Nwas a man who was as big as a giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.61,0:24:11.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But he turned out to be a very kind person.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.02,0:24:14.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"The Night in Adelaide".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.72,0:24:15.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
